<p>I have an element with a vertical scrollbar on auto. In IE7, once the scrollbar appears, the child element reduces width(as that much width is taken by the scrollbar). Now when you click again the child element does not regain its width even though the scrollbar has disappeared.</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>$('.a').click(function () {     $('.a').toggleClass('short'); });</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>.a {     position: relative;     width: 300px;     height: 500px;     overflow-y: auto;     background-color: red; } .a.short {     height: 300px; } .b {     position: relative;     height: 400px;     background-color: blue; }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.1/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;div class="a"&gt;     &lt;div class="b"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>